var mu = lambda * epsilon
	if (sigma == 0.000001 && alpha != 1.0) return NaN
	var ret = simClaDS1( tree, lambda, alpha, sigma, mu, rho )
	
	return ret
ppl:
var tree = phyjs.bisse_32
	var particles = 5000
	var MAX_LAMBDA = 5
	var MAX_DIV = 5
	var MIN_LAMBDA = 0.00001
	var PANDA = false
var model = function()
{
	var sigma = 1
	var alpha = 1
	var epsilon = 0.065
	var lambda = 0.81
	var rho = 1
	
	var mu = lambda * epsilon
	if (sigma == 0.000001 && alpha != 1.0) return NaN
	var ret = simClaDS1( tree, lambda, alpha, sigma, mu, rho )
	
	return ret
}
var dist = Infer({method: 'SMC', particles: particles, model: model})
dist.normalizationConstant
